Definition.WordDefinition:
GAMMA
<language> 1. A language for matrices and generation of mathematical programming reports.
["GAMMA 3.3 for MPS/MPSX, IBM System:/360", Bonnor & Moore Assocs (Mar 1975)].
2. A high-level parallel language.
[Research Directions in High-Level Parallel Languages, LeMetayer ed, Springer 1992].
(1994-11-29)

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: gamma \gam"ma\ (g[a^]m"m[.a]), n. The third letter ([Gamma], [gamma] = Eng. G) of the Greek alphabet. [1913 Webster]

gamma n 1: the 3rd letter of the Greek alphabet 2: a unit of magnetic field strength equal to one-hundred-thousandth of an oersted 3: Portuguese navigator who led an expedition around the Cape of Good Hope in 1497; he sighted and named Natal on Christmas Day before crossing the Indian Ocean (1469-1524) [syn: {da Gamma}, {Vasco da Gamma}]
